  "texts": [
    "It is important to make a distinction between two types of PAC bounds.",
    "Theorem 1.2 is usually refered to as an empirical bound.",
    "It means that, for any θ, R(θ) is upper bounded by an empirical quantity, that is, by something that we can compute when we observe the data.",
    "This allows to study the ERM as the minimizer of this bound.",
    "It also provides a numerical certificate of the generalization error of the ERM."
  ],
